ahd: pic#0","article":"I am not an expert at Polish, but I know some languages have multiple words for \"you\" at different levels of formality. Formal \"you\" sometimes gets translated as \"thou\"; this seems in the same vein.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"5 years ago","below":14412203,"ctime":"August 4 2011, 21:03:34 UTC","parent":14406059,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://garzahd.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"garzahd","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"garzahd","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://garzahd.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"garzahd","ctime_ts":1312491814,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/109903244/37354368","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/230827.html?thread=14412203#t14412203","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/230827.html?thread=14412203#t14412203","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/230827.html?thread=14412203#t14412203","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_513015","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100000453073957","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":14412203,"talkid":56297,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/230827.html?thread=14412203#t14412203","above":14407595,"upictitle":"Karol Andrzejewski: pic#109903244","article":"Yes, it's a quirk. 'Pan' means something like lord or sir and has no direct translation to English. It is formal and you use it when you address a stranger or a person you respect, etc.<br /><br />On the other hand I see that lots of people as much as worships George here in Poland. This 'Lord' may not be very far away from the truth. ;)","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"5 years ago","ctime":"August 5 2011, 10:49:27 UTC","parent":14406059,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100000453073957","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Karol Andrzejewski","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_513015","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=37354368&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Karol Andrzejewski","ctime_ts":1312541367,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/230827.html?thread=14427819#t14427819","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/230827.html?thread=14427819#t14427819","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/230827.html?thread=14427819#t14427819","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"wersy2","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://wersy2.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":14427819,"talkid":56358,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/230827.html?thread=14427819#t14427819","above":14412203,"upictitle":"wersy2: pic#0","article":"Ha! Yeah, it can mean \"lord\" as well, a bit like Spanish \"senor\":)<br /><br />This tradition stems from the old custom of the Polish nobility to call themselves \"panowie bracia\"(the lord brothers/fraternal lords, to stress the fact they all considered themselves equal to each other, or at least that was the idea) which, as the time passed, spread throughout all the society. For obvious reasons, the commies hated this way of adressing each other and hence they tried hard to replace it 